    dc:title "Geophagus pyrineusi: a new species from the rio Teles Pires, rio Tapajós basin, Brazil (Cichliformes: Cichlidae: Geophagini)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796665>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796677>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796675>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796679>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796671> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796665>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Polymorphism and ontogenetic variation in Geophagus pyrineusi, new species. A. Holotype, MZUSP 119715, 94.1 mm SL. B. Paratype, MZUSP 119716, 94.1 mm SL. C. Paratype, MZUSP 121509, 110.1 mm SL. D. Paratype, MZUSP 118122, 112.1 mm SL. Notice that the presence and shape of melanophoric marks varies slightly between the two sides in some specimens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6796665/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796677>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Melanophoric marks present in Geophagus pyrineusi, new species (some marks absent in some specimens). DMP, dorsal melanophoric patch; FB, flank bar; RB, residual bar; LMP, lateral melanophoric patch." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6796677/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796675>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Geophagus pyrineusi immediately after capture; both paratypes from Brazil, State of Mato Grosso. A. MZUSP 118122, 112.1 mm SL, rio Cristalino. B. MZUSP 119717, 82.1 mm SL, rio Teles Pires." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6796675/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796679>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Geographic distribution and habitat of Geophagus pyrineusi. A. Map of the central portion of the rio Tapajós basin, showing the type locality (white circle) and additional localities (red stars) from where G. pyrineusi is known. B. Type locality, Brazil, Mato Grosso, Alta Floresta, rio Cristalino, tributary of rio Teles Pires, rio Tapajós basin. Photo by Cléber Ricardo dos Santos." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6796679/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6796671>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Geophagus pyrineusi, preserved paratypes; both from Brazil, State of Mato Grosso. A. MZUSP 121509, 110.1 mm SL, right view, rio Cristalino. B. MNRJ 1277, 78.7 mm SL, rio Teles Pires." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6796671/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

